he bait: the e5 pawn looks free, but the knight on d4 and the queen ready for g5 are setting an ambush."},{"nodeId":"n2","text":"The strike: Qg5! threatens both the knight on e5 and the g2 pawn at once — White is already lost.","shapes":[{"orig":"g5","dest":"e5","brush":"green"},{"orig":"g5","dest":"g2","brush":"green"}]},{"nodeId":"n8","text":"The finish: after Qxg2, Rf1, Qxe4+ and Be2, Nf3 delivers a smothered mate."}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'blackburne-shilling-gambit';
