,{"nodeId":"n8","text":"The finish: …but Bb4+! Qd2 Bxd2+ Kxd2 Kxd8 recovers the queen and leaves Black a piece up."}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'elephant-trap';
update traps set body_en = '{"intro":"Draft pending review. The Mortimer Trap: the odd-looking 4...Ne7 invites White to take e5, but a fork lies in wait.","tree":{"nodes":{"n0":{"id":"n0","parentId":null,"ply":0,"san":null,"uci":null,"fen":"r1bqkb1r/ppppnppp/5n2/1B2p3/4P3/3P1N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 1 5","children":["n1","n7"]},"n1":{"id":"n1","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Nxe5","uci":"f3e5","fen":"r1bqkb1r/ppppnppp/5n2/1B2N3/4P3/3P4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R b KQkq - 0 5","children":["n2"]},"n2":{"id":"n2","parentId":"n1","ply":2,"san":"c6","uci":"c7c6","fen":"r1bqkb1r/pp1pnppp/2p2n2/1B2N3/4P3/3P4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 6","children":["n3"]},"n3":{"id":"n3","parentId":"n2","ply":3,"san":"Bc4","uci":"b5c4","fen":"r1bqkb1r/pp1pnppp/2p2n2/4N3/2B1P3/3P4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R b KQkq - 1 6","children":["n4"]},"n4":{"id":"n4","parentId":"n3","ply":4,"san":"Qa5+","uci":"d8a5","fen":"r1b1kb1r/pp1pnppp/2p2n2/q3N3/2B1P3/3P4/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 2 7","children":["n5"]},"n5":{"id":"n5","parentId":"n4","ply":5,"san":"Nc3","uci":"b1c3","fen":"r1b1kb1r/pp1pnppp/2p2n2/q3N3/2B1P3/2NP4/PPP2PPP/R1BQK2R b KQkq - 3 7","children":["n6"]},"n6":{"id":"n6","parentId":"n5","ply":6,"san":"Qxe5","uci":"a5e5","fen":"r1b1kb1r/pp1pnppp/2p2n2/4q3/2B1P3/2NP4/PPP2PPP/R1BQK2R w KQkq - 0 8","children":[]},"n7":{"id":"n7","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"O-O","uci":"e1g1","fen":"r1bqkb1r/ppppnppp/5n2/1B2p3/4P3/3P1N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 2 5","children":[],"comment":"Better not to take e5: just develop quietly."}},"rootId":"n0","seq":8},"steps":[{"nodeId":"n1","text":"The bait: e5 looks like a free pawn after the odd Ne7, but that is exactly the invitation of the trap."},{"nodeId":"n4","text":"The strike: c6 drives the bishop away and then Qa5+ forks the king and the knight on e5.","shapes":[{"orig":"a5","dest":"e5","brush":"green"},{"orig":"a5","dest":"e1","brush":"green"}]},{"nodeId":"n6","text":"The finish: Black wins the knight back with Qxe5, ending up a piece ahead."}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'trappola-di-mortimer';
update traps set body_en = '{"intro":"Draft pending review. The Englund Trap: the black queen raids b2 and, if White plays Bc3, a back-rank mate strikes.","tree":{"nodes":{"n0":{"id":"n0","parentId":null,"ply":0,"san":null,"uci":null,"fen":"r1b1kbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/5N2/PqPBPPPP/RN1QKB1R w KQkq - 0 6","children":["n1","n7"]},"n1":{"id":"n1","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Bc3","uci":"d2c3","fen":"r1b1kbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/2B2N2/PqP1PPPP/RN1QKB1R b KQkq - 1 6","children":["n2"]},"n2":{"id":"n2","parentId":"n1","ply":2,"san":"Bb4","uci":"f8b4","fen":"r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/1b6/2B2N2/PqP1PPPP/RN1QKB1R w KQkq - 2 7","children":["n3"]},"n3":{"id":"n3","parentId":"n2","ply":3,"san":"Qd2","uci":"d1d2","fen":"r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/1b6/2B2N2/PqPQPPPP/RN2KB1R b KQkq - 3 7","children":["n4"]},"n4":{"id":"n4","parentId":"n3","ply":4,"san":"Bxc3","uci":"b4c3","fen":"r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/2b2N2/PqPQPPPP/RN2KB1R w KQkq - 0 8","children":["n5"]},"n5":{"id":"n5","parentId":"n4","ply":5,"san":"Qxc3","uci":"d2c3","fen":"r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/2Q2N2/PqP1PPPP/RN2KB1R b KQkq - 0 8","children":["n6"]},"n6":{"id":"n6","parentId":"n5","ply":6,"san":"Qc1#","uci":"b2c1","fen":"r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/2Q2N2/P1P1PPPP/RNq1KB1R w KQkq - 1 9","children":[]},"n7":{"id":"n7","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Nc3","uci":"b1c3","fen":"r1b1kbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/8/2N2N2/PqPBPPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 1 6","children":[],"comment":"Defends b2 and a1 without falling for it: 6.Nc3."}},"rootId":"n0","seq":8},"steps":[{"nodeId":"n1","text":"The bait: Bc3 attacks the queen on b2 and seems to trap it, but it is White who ends up trapped."},{"nodeId":"n2","text":"The strike: Bb4! pins the c3 bishop against the king — it can no longer capture the queen.","shapes":[{"orig":"b4","dest":"e1","brush":"green"}]},{"nodeId":"n6","text":"The finish: Bxc3, Qxc3 and Qc1 is mate — the white king is smothered by its own pieces."}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'gambetto-englund';
update traps set body_en = '{"intro":"Draft pending review. The Kieninger Trap in the Budapest: 6.Nbd2? leads to a smothered mate on d3, thanks to the pin on e2.","tree":{"nodes":{"n0":{"id":"n0","parentId":null,"ply":0,"san":null,"uci":null,"fen":"r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/1bP2Bn1/5N2/PP2PPPP/RN1QKB1R w KQkq - 5 6","children":["n1","n7"]},"n1":{"id":"n1","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Nbd2","uci":"b1d2","fen":"r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/1bP2Bn1/5N2/PP1NPPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 6 6","children":["n2"]},"n2":{"id":"n2","parentId":"n1","ply":2,"san":"Qe7","uci":"d8e7","fen":"r1b1k2r/ppppqppp/2n5/4P3/1bP2Bn1/5N2/PP1NPPPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 7 7","children":["n3"]},"n3":{"id":"n3","parentId":"n2","ply":3,"san":"a3","uci":"a2a3","fen":"r1b1k2r/ppppqppp/2n5/4P3/1bP2Bn1/P4N2/1P1NPPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 0 7","children":["n4"]},"n4":{"id":"n4","parentId":"n3","ply":4,"san":"Ngxe5","uci":"g4e5","fen":"r1b1k2r/ppppqppp/2n5/4n3/1bP2B2/P4N2/1P1NPPPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 0 8","children":["n5"]},"n5":{"id":"n5","parentId":"n4","ply":5,"san":"axb4","uci":"a3b4","fen":"r1b1k2r/ppppqppp/2n5/4n3/1PP2B2/5N2/1P1NPPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 0 8","children":["n6"]},"n6":{"id":"n6","parentId":"n5","ply":6,"san":"Nd3#","uci":"e5d3","fen":"r1b1k2r/ppppqppp/2n5/8/1PP2B2/3n1N2/1P1NPPPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 1 9","children":[]},"n7":{"id":"n7","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Nc3","uci":"b1c3","fen":"r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n5/4P3/1bP2Bn1/2N2N2/PP2PPPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 6 6","children":[],"comment":"The correct way to block: 6.Nc3, and there is no trap."}},"rootId":"n0","seq":8},"steps":[{"nodeId":"n1","text":"The bait: blocking the check with Nbd2 is natural, but it leaves the king trapped by its own pieces."},{"nodeId":"n4","text":"The strike: the queen on e7 pins the e2 pawn; Ngxe5 sets up the finishing blow.","shapes":[{"orig":"e7","dest":"e2","brush":"green"}]},{"nodeId":"n6","text":"The finish: Nd3 is mate — the e2 pawn, pinned by the queen, cannot capture the knight.","shapes":[{"orig":"e5","dest":"d3","brush":"green"}]}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'trappola-kieninger-budapest';
update traps set body_en = '{"intro":"Draft pending review. The Damiano (2...f6) is one of the worst moves: White sacrifices on e5 and gets a winning attack.","tree":{"nodes":{"n0":{"id":"n0","parentId":null,"ply":0,"san":null,"uci":null,"fen":"rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/4p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2","children":["n1","n9"]},"n1":{"id":"n1","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"f6","uci":"f7f6","fen":"rnbqkbnr/pppp2pp/5p2/4p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 3","children":["n2"]},"n2":{"id":"n2","parentId":"n1","ply":2,"san":"Nxe5","uci":"f3e5","fen":"rnbqkbnr/pppp2pp/5p2/4N3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 0 3","children":["n3"]},"n3":{"id":"n3","parentId":"n2","ply":3,"san":"fxe5","uci":"f6e5","fen":"rnbqkbnr/pppp2pp/8/4p3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 4","children":["n4"]},"n4":{"id":"n4","parentId":"n3","ply":4,"san":"Qh5+","uci":"d1h5","fen":"rnbqkbnr/pppp2pp/8/4p2Q/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1KB1R b KQkq - 1 4","children":["n5"]},"n5":{"id":"n5","parentId":"n4","ply":5,"san":"Ke7","uci":"e8e7","fen":"rnbq1bnr/ppppk1pp/8/4p2Q/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1KB1R w KQ - 2 5","children":["n6"]},"n6":{"id":"n6","parentId":"n5","ply":6,"san":"Qxe5+","uci":"h5e5","fen":"rnbq1bnr/ppppk1pp/8/4Q3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1KB1R b KQ - 0 5","children":["n7"]},"n7":{"id":"n7","parentId":"n6","ply":7,"san":"Kf7","uci":"e7f7","fen":"rnbq1bnr/pppp1kpp/8/4Q3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1KB1R w KQ - 1 6","children":["n8"]},"n8":{"id":"n8","parentId":"n7","ply":8,"san":"Bc4+","uci":"f1c4","fen":"rnbq1bnr/pppp1kpp/8/4Q3/2B1P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNB1K2R b KQ - 2 6","children":[]},"n9":{"id":"n9","parentId":"n0","ply":1,"san":"Nc6","uci":"b8c6","fen":"r1bqkbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/4p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 2 3","children":[],"comment":"The sound move: defend e5 with a piece, not with ...f6."}},"rootId":"n0","seq":10},"steps":[{"nodeId":"n1","text":"The bait: defending e5 with ...f6 weakens the king and the diagonal toward e8 — this is the Damiano Defense.","shapes":[{"orig":"d1","dest":"h5","brush":"red"}]},{"nodeId":"n2","text":"The strike: Nxe5! If Black takes (...fxe5), Qh5+ follows with a furious attack."},{"nodeId":"n8","text":"The finish: Qxe5+ and Bc4+ unleash a winning attack on the exposed king (draft: clear advantage for White)."}]}'::jsonb where slug = 'difesa-damiano';
